A Ghanaian footballer playing for a South African team accidentally thanked both his wife and his girlfriend after scoring two goals, on a video posted on YouTube. Free State Stars striker Mohammed Anas gave an interview after a 2-2 match against Ajax Cape Town, saying he thanked God for his performance. “I appreciate my fans also, my wife and my girlfriend,” the 22-year-old added. He then tried to correct his mistake: “I mean my wife, sorry.” The video posted over the weekend sparked amused comments, with one of them simply saying: “Too late…”(NAN)